OL,3,CAlmost half of Welsh workers
OL,4,Cexperience sexual harassment, survey
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,FA survey of 2000 employees across
OL,8,FWales found 43% of men and 48% of
OL,9,Fwomen reported experiencing sexual
OL,10,Fharassment at work; with highest
OL,11,Fprevalence in the architecture,
OL,12,Fengineering, and building industries
OL,13,F(66%).
OL,15,FAlthough around half of respondents
OL,16,Fdid report their sexual harassment, a
OL,17,Ffurther 7% did not report incidents of
OL,18,Fharassments for fear of impacting
OL,19,Ftheir career, and 10% did not trust
OL,20,Fthat they'd be believed by the
OL,21,Femployer.
